    "body": "@nventuro:\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\nNot critical, but is this going to be fixed soon?\r\n\r\nAlso, not directly related, but I'm not sure where else to ask this:\r\nWhen is the next formal release expected, and where can I generally find future release dates and versions?\r\n\r\nWe need to do our own release soon, and since OpenZeppelin code is embedded mostly into our two Token contracts, it will not be upgradable on our system (can replace \"inner\" contracts, but not the ones which hold the actual balance).\r\n\r\nSo we would ideally like to have a verified version of OpenZeppelin (and even more ideally, a x.0.0 kind of version).\r\n\r\nThank you, and I apologize for posting this possibly in the wrong place.",
