    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've opened a PR fixing this (#1169), you can see it on this very same issue.\r\n\r\nThe next release (1.12) is actually coming out today, and the next version after that is 2.0, coming out in about a month. You can look at the 2.0 milestone and related issues/PRs [here](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/milestone/3). There will probably be a blogpost soon describing what 2.0 entails.\r\n\r\nThat said, OpenZeppelin code has been around for quite a bit and is used by multiple projects, so I'm not sure what sort of extra 'verification' you're expecting. Small issues like this don't really affect the smart contract code, but rather the maintainability of the project.\r\n\r\nBy the way, if you're interested in upgradeability, take a look at [ZeppelinOS](https://zeppelinos.org/), which tackles that issue head-on.",
