    "body": "@nventuro:\r\n\r\nOf course, I wasn't referring to those minor changes in JS files.\r\nBut I've been updating from your repo every once in a while, and on my last update (yesterday), I noticed that you have merged `BasicToken` into `StandardToken`.\r\nThis by itself is also not a fundamental change as far as I could tell, but it is nevertheless a lot more relevant to my concern.\r\n\r\nI am pretty confident with your verification infrastructure (and I've been running it locally on both `truffle test` and `solidity-coverage`, so I also know that it covers 100% of statements/functions/branches/lines).\r\nThe only really concern here is \"formality\", i.e., we will need to be able to state that our code uses an official release of OpenZeppelin.\r\n\r\nRegarding upgradability, we already have our own (proprietary) solution of an AddressManager contract.\r\nIt's a pretty simple solution, and I am reluctant to change it at this point.\r\n\r\nThanks again!",
