    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ahh, I see that those recent changes that I just mentioned are not there yet.\r\nThis means that I am going to have to rewind all my recent updates.\r\nAny chance they are included in the upcoming release today?\r\n\r\nAlso, in general, you suggestion for `npm install openzeppelin-solidity` is somewhat problematic for me.\r\nMy ecosystem is based on Truffle, which expects to find all contracts under the same (`contracts`) folder.\r\nThis means that to begin with, I will need to add a `postinstall` script to my `package.json` file, which will copy your contracts from folder `/node_modules/openzeppelin-solidity/contracts` into folder `/contracts`.\r\nSecond, we use only a subset of your contracts, but this is minor.\r\nThird, we use a modified version of your `MintableToken` contract (so again, a `postinstall` script is required).\r\n\r\nBy the way, `npm install` does not download your [mocks](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/tree/master/contracts/mocks) folder, so I will not even be able to run your tests.",
