    "body": "There is no need for you to run our tests locally, since they've been run for each single build. \r\n\r\nTruffle also **will** recognize modules installed with npm (it is our main usage scenario), you just need to do e.g. `import \"openzeppelin-zos/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol\";`.\r\n\r\nRegarding the `MintableToken` change, I would recommend against modifying OpenZeppelin code, and doing the changes you require via inheritance, if at all possible. What is it about the contract that doesn't suit your project's needs?",
