    "body": "@nventuro:\r\n\r\nI use `truffle` for testing, but `solc` for compiling (i.e., for deploying eventually).\r\nSo if I understand your suggestion correctly, then I would be forced to use different import paths inside my contracts (one for `truffle` and one for `solc`).\r\nAnd that would require some sort of project configuration within an IDE (which I am currently not using, and I'm not even aware of any such tool for Solidity, to be honest).\r\nAm I wrong?\r\n\r\nWith regards to the `Mintable` contract, we changed the `mint` function from:\r\n```\r\n    hasMintPermission canMint public\r\n```\r\nTo:\r\n```\r\n    internal\r\n```\r\nThis is because we have our own internal mechanism for minting at certain points.\r\n\r\nBy the way, `npm install` does not download your [mocks](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/tree/master/contracts/mocks) folder.",
