    "body": "I don't have any hard data on this, but would expect most people to use `truffle` (or a very similar alternative). The main reason behind this is not so much the compilation itself, but the need to develop tests for your contracts: `truffle` comes integrated with `ganache-cli`, `mocha`, web3, and provides the `truffle-contracts` wrapper, so doing this is remarkably simple. \r\n\r\nIs there a specific reason why you want to call `solc` directly from the command line? From what I understand, you used to simply copy the code over, and that worked. What about testing?",
